This paper deals with the procedural generation of levels in video games, which is a problem that falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses evolutionary algorithms, which are a popular machine learning technique, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. The paper also involves graphics and simulations, which could fall under cs.GR. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to evaluate the generated levels, which could fall under cs.CV. Finally, the paper discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different approaches, which could fall under cs.GT (computer science and game theory).
